# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Here I provide other idea from backtracking. I prefer to use DP. The backtracking solution can be used to solve the similar question.
[46. Permutations
](https://leetcode.com/problems/permutations/solutions/3850602/cpython-bitmask-backtrackingbeats-100/)
Let's solve it by Math. Consider the set n choose k denoted as
$$ 
C_k^n=\{\{i_1,\cdots, i_k\}|1\leq i_1<\cdots< i_k\leq n\}
$$
then, it follows
$$
C_k^n=C_k^{n-1}\bigcup C_{with\ n}^n
$$
where
$$
C_{with\ n}^n=\{\{i_1,\cdots, i_k\}|1\leq i_1<\cdots<i_{k-1}< i_k= n\}
$$.
The crucial part is that there exists an one-to-one correspondence between the sets $C_{k-1}^{n-1}$ and $C_{with\ n}^n$ with
$$
v\in C_{k-1}^{n-1} \longrightarrow v\cup \{n \} \in C_{with\ n}^n.
$$
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Use unordered_map( based own hash), recursion with memoization to implement this idea.

2nd version uses map.

3rd version uses 4D array as DP state matrix.
# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(n choose k)
- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
 O(n * k)

# Code
```
using int2=pair<int, int>;
struct pair_hash
{
    size_t operator() (const int2& pair) const {
        return hash<int>()(pair.first) ^ hash<int>()(pair.second);
    }
};
class Solution {
public:
    unordered_map<int2, vector<vector<int>>, pair_hash> mp;

    vector<vector<int>> comb(int n, int k){
        if (n==1 && k==1) return mp[{1,1}]={{1}};
        if (mp.count({n, k})!=0) return mp[{n, k}];
        vector<vector<int>> ans={};
        if (k==1){
            for(int x=1; x<=n; x++) ans.push_back({x});
        } 
        else if (n==k){
            ans.resize(1);
            for(int x=1; x<=n; x++) ans[0].push_back(x);
        }
        else{
            ans=comb(n-1, k);
            vector<vector<int>> c_wo_n=comb(n-1, k-1);
            for (vector<int>& v: c_wo_n){
                vector<int> v_w_n=v;
                v_w_n.push_back(n);
                ans.push_back(v_w_n);
            }
        }
        return mp[{n, k}]=ans;
    }
    vector<vector<int>> combine(int n, int k) {
        return comb(n, k);
    }
};
```
