# Approach
1. We have to choose exactly K numbers out of N numbers.
2. To choose that we will create bit masks.
3. What bit masks will do is, we have all the numbers which have only K set bits and it is less than 2^N (i.e. total number of bits are less equal to N) so these will help to choose the K numbers. 

So what we did is : 
- Saare numbers genrate kar liye jisne K set bits hai.
- Jin position ki bit set hai unko ek array m push kra 
- Usko result m push kr diya


# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(2^N * log(N))
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: O(log K)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    // ye function ek number ko lega aur usme jis position 
    // pr set bit (1) hai usko array m push krega 
    vector<int> fun(int num)
    {
       vector<int> ans;
       int cnt=1;
       while(num)
       {
           if(num%2) ans.emplace_back(cnt);
           num/=2;
           cnt++;
       }
       return ans;
    }
    vector<vector<int>> combine(int n, int k) {
        vector<vector<int>> ans;
        // (1<<n) = 2^n
        // Loop chala do 2^N taki saare numbers aa jaaye 
        for(int i=0; i< (1<<n) ; i++) 
        {
            // Jis numbers mai bits exactly K hai vo he kaam k hai bs
            if(__builtin_popcount(i) == k) 
            ans.emplace_back(fun(i));
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
```

